title: For Sale:  Caspian Custom Gold Cup Style 1911 45 Colt style         NightSight racegun National Match Barrel 7791193
postcontent: For your consideration is a well made, solid, and very reliable Gold Cup Style Caspian Custom full size 1911 with the Caspian integral MagWell. This gun was made by a very good private GunSmith, utilizing all quality parts. The gun was fitted with an (oldschool spot-on) point of aim shooting American Military Colt/Springfield National Match team barrel with the 7791193 number rollmark. I am not a history perfectionist about the 779 NM barrels, but I did research the net like crazy to conclude this as factual. The National Match numbers are shown on the barrel hood in the photos and match the time line of the U.S. Military's 1960's production barrels (sometime around or before 1963). This barrel is hard as the dickens and was RC hardness tested by my GunSmith to prove it. He schooled me on the fascinating history of military barrels and all the great stories behind them. It is configured and fit to shoot fast and on target. This entire 1911 gun has a dark Parkerized type color, which is a PolyKote/duracoat Baked on type finish. Please stop to look at the great condition and nice looking 45 Gold Cup style 1911. It has a really nice flat top and serrations, Gold Cup Style like the Colt Gold Cup. Please also review the photos to see the Gun's set up and well put together configuration. This very well balanced and professionally fitted combo, sports a full size 5 inch 7791193 Match/Military barrel. The Slide to frame fit was well executed and the gun is filled with good parts. This oldschool Goldcup Style 1911 was outfitted with a real nicely lined up sight combination with a front night sight shown in the photos, that blows away the 10 Ring on targets. I personally test fired it with my local GunSmith Steve Fischer who is a well known GunSmith here in Florida. We were impressed by the old National Match barrel. The rear sight is really nicely lined up to the GoldCup style flat top serrations, making it a nice aesthetic combination. The gun was neatly fit overall and has functioning a Match grade extractor and ejector fitted to it. The hammer is a Chip McKormick Kimber style hammer. The Caspian frame also has a high ride Chip McKormick grip safety fitted to it for a high hold grip so you can line up a nice point of aim shot. This full size metal monster has a great Magwell and Kimber grip set, which provides a positive purchase grip when held. This nice grip it has also helps to blast your target's bullseye away. The frame Magwell and high hold allows fast magazine reloads. It has an ingenious Caspain integral MagWell that really does make a real difference when reloading. As you can see in the photos, it also has a race extended Magazine thumb release for super speedy reloading action. It was coated very nicely, as shown in the pictures and sports some nice and neat Kimber full size magazine-well grips. This gun is a nice treat to take to the range or to your local 1911 gun shooting competition. It has a very low round count, which were fired during the professional test fire my GunSmith performed. I got to shoot a couple magazines worth while he test fired it and I was impressed with the GoldCup style flat top sight plain, and it's sight line up. I am pricing this one lower than my other high end auctions, for what should be an easy and quick sale. It handles more like shooting a 6 inch or 7 inch length barrel 1911, because this gun is solid steel throughout the entire gun. It is filled with quality american parts. I will hate to see this gun go but I need the money. It's another 1911 work of art I photographed with a high quality and high resolution digital camera with 14 megapixels. So what you see is what you get, and is without a doubt quite the shooter for race competition or home defense. This 1911 comes with one Colt magazine that was tuned to the gun by Professional Master GunSmith Steve Fischer, from here in Sunny South Florida. Happy bidding and good luck. Thank you for looking at my auctions. There will be more to come so keep in tune. Before we move on to the rules and payment section of the description... Please allow me to take this time to expand on Fischer's background and facts, as a true Master GunSmith. Steve Fischer is an old buddy of the world famous Wayne Novak, whom I have had the pleasure of meeting. They went to GunSmith School together in the same Class in Colorado over three decades ago, and they graduated from the GunSmith school together. Both men graduating from the same class set out to be partners and legends. They started their careers together working for Armand Swenson. Swenson stole the first idea on Dovetail sights that Wayne Novak firstly invented back then. After a confrontation in regards to this fall out with Swenson... Novak and Fischer quit. Both acclaimed men told me the story along the lines of that in addition to Wayne's idea and first sight design being robbed of him... they both told me the story with a smile, that the Armand parts were out of spec all the time and so hard to work with. They both claim and explained, they "made one gun in the time they could have made 4 if they were using better parts." So they learned a hard lesson and broke free, quitting Swenson's "sweatshop" and workbench. They left the mediocre Armand Swenson outfit and assembly line, to begin their personal rise above the rest of the 1911 world at the time. They began expanding their explosive careers as GunSmiths, and the rest as you know is history. We all know Wayne Novak for his sights and great gunwork. Steve Fischer, Novak's old colleague went on to work for Colt as one of the lead GunSmiths. From there Steve Fischer went onward to open his own successful GunSmith operation, which has stayed open in sunny south Florida for over 3 decades. Steve is also a champ competition shooter, and he still wins Shotgun matches held yearly in Minneapolis to this day. Additionally Steve is so Old-School, he even knows how to shoot from the hip and smokes the competition in whatever style of shooting he chooses. He looks like a battle troll when I go shooting with him. It is a strange unexpected and powerful metamorphosis to see this 71 year old man go from a regular guy into shooting mode. It almost looks like an ora glows around him and he transforms into like some kind of troll or a stalky looking battle dwarf-thing from Lord of the Rings. A real treat to learn from and have as a friend. I have seen the old battle hound at work and it is no joke. Fischer is also the first GunSmith to make a compensated 40 caliber 1911, shown in an old 80's Gun News Gun Magazine back in the year 1980. Steve worked and built up the gun shown in the photos, helping to make it a real master piece in gun mechanics. In addition to the work Fischer did on this gun for me to tune it up, Fischer tuned a nice magazine up to be mated to this speedy and highly responsive race gun... What Fischer did was he timed and tested the innards of the mag in mention, utilizing a CobraMag spring for this gun's Colt Magazine. F.y.i. CobraMag and CobrMag parts are made by the ever famous 2010 American PistolSmith Guild's award winner. Whose CobraMag from Trippreasearch dot com, holds the world record of the only 1911 magazine to pass a 55,000 (sick and grueling) round test without failure. That's right, astounding and out of this world! You heard/read it right... 55,000 rounds blasting off without a hiccup, jam, or hitch. Damn that is a nasty record my friends!!! So in other words this gun including the magazine has been tuned to run superbly for your enjoyment at the range, shooting tactical course, or save your bacon in a self defense situation when the chips are down with your a** on the line. title: For Sale/Trade:  Mixed Lot - 2 Rolls Washington 90% Silver Quarters
postcontent:
Mixed Lot - 2 Rolls of 1964 and earlier 90% Silver Washington circulated quarters plus one standing liberty quarter (junk) with no date. 81 coins in total. Many are in XF & VF condition (see photo). All dates and mint marks are read-able on the Washington quarters and are not junk coins.

Silver coins are the most dynamic form of silver in that they serve as both a type of bullion investment and as a collectible. Though some coins are more expensive than others, virtually all of them are going to be sold at a fair amount over the spot price of silver per ounce.
The reason that coins cost more than a round or bar of comparable weight is found in their scarcity and, in return, their demand. Coins have a much higher secondary market demand than any other piece of silver because they canât simply be replicated at will. A bar, round, or other piece of raw silver can be minted by any company. A coin, on the other hand, is usually produced in liamited quantities and is only made by one particular mint. In the end, coins are very popular among collectors, and when you combine that with the value of silver you will end up with an expensive item.
